This directory contains tests for the PNG and TTF parses and in future will include any other formats it
they will be implemnted.

You can run tests in two modes:

* Regular:
	$ make test-ttf
	$ make test-png
	$ make test-wav
	$ make test-map

  There are tests for the logic itself, that everything works and parses correctly. The two commands above
  output ttf.ppm and png.ppm everywhere. Strictly speaking these tests are not fully automated. Aside from
  a few exceptions where the program fails to output anything at all, you must determine whether the test
  passed by inspecting the final output yourself.

* Fuzzing:
	$ make fuzz-ttf
	$ make fuzz-png
	$ make fuzz-wav
	$ make fuzz-map

  These test for any vulnerabilities or C bugs like UB. Passing here is considered when fuzzing lasted
  15 minutes without any errors. If any errors occured during the process you will see them.  

  They are ran automatically by Github CI but you should not rely on them as I am just economing free
  minutes there. If you change any of the parsers and willing to commit to this repository, run fuzzies
  on your machine for full 15 minutes.
